                     <interp inst="t18280110-219-off1151" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18280110-219-cd1152" type="crimeDate">21st of December</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280110-219-off1151 t18280110-219-cd1152"></join>, 2 pairs of boots, value 5s.
            </rs>, the goods 
               <persName id="t18280110-219-victim1301" type="victimName">
                  Robert 
                  Langford
               <interp inst="t18280110-219-victim1301" type="surname" value="Langford"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280110-219-victim1301" type="given" value="Robert"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280110-219-victim1301" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280110-219-off1151 t18280110-219-victim1301"></join>
                  </persName>
            .</p>
               <p>THOMAS DAVIS. I live with Robert Langford, a <rs id="t18280110-219-viclabel1153" type="occupation">boot and shoe-maker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280110-219-victim1301 t18280110-219-viclabel1153"></join>, of <placeName id="t18280110-219-crimeloc1154">Cripplegate</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280110-219-crimeloc1154" type="placeName" value="Cripplegate"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280110-219-crimeloc1154" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280110-219-off1151 t18280110-219-crimeloc1154"></join>. I did not see these boots taken, but I had seen them two minutes before, on a horse in the shop - the prisoner came in to look at a pair of boy's boots; I showed her a pair - she did not like them; she offered 3s. 6d. for another pair, which I could not take - she left, and came back, and asked for a pair of boy's spencers, which were in a case, and while I got them, she must have put these boots into her apron: Sarah Davis came up, and asked what was in her apron; she said nothing - but these boots were found in it.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. PHILLIPS. Q. Was she not talking to you about boots at this very time? A. No.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280110-219-person1302">
                  SARAH 
                  DAVIS
               <interp inst="t18280110-219-person1302" type="surname" value="DAVIS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280110-219-person1302" type="given" value="SARAH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280110-219-person1302" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was coming down stairs, and saw the prisoner take two pairs of boots off the horse, and put them into her apron; I asked what she had there; she said nothing - but I took them from her apron.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182801100104"></xptr>JOSEPH ORTON. I am an officer, and took her in charge- I found 4s. on her - she is married, and has two children.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 30.</p>
